labeled “Cubist” and proposed a radically different understanding of the movement. At Rosenberg’s Galerie L’Effort Moderne in Paris, artists such as Joseph Csáky, Auguste Herbin, Jean Metzinger, Diego Rivera, Gino Severini, and Georges Valmier were accorded the same treatment as Pablo Picasso or Georges Braque. In this book, Casini considers Rosenberg’s contribution to the history of Cubism, reflecting on the ways in which artistic movements are manufactured—and interpretive paradigms adopted.Deftly weaving biography with a scholarly analysis built on extensive archival research, Léonce Rosenberg’s Cubism is a fresh look at the history of interwar modernism and the definitive study of a figure who has been unjustly sidelined in the history of art. It will be compulsory reading for scholars of Cubism and Modernism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aArt dealerszFrancezParisvBiography. 0aCubismzFrancezParis. 7aART / History / Modern (late 19th Century to 1945).2bisacsh  aAbstraction.  aAmbroise Vollard.  aArt Market.  aCubism.  aGalerie L’Effort Moderne.  aInterwar Period.  aJewish Dealers.  aKahnweiler.  aLéonce Rosenberg.  aModernism.  aNetworks.  aParis.  aPaul Guillaume.  aPaul Rosenberg.  aReturn to order.  apost-war classicism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2023z9783111318103oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2023 Englishz978311131903208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780271096025?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780271096025423Coveruhttps://www.de